President Obama has announced his intention to nominate Constance Smith Barker for the position of Commissioner at the Equal Employment Opportunity Commission. Barker is currently serving her second term as Commissioner and has previously worked as a shareholder at the law firm of Capell & Howard, P.C. in Alabama. She has also served as General Counsel to the Mobile County Public School System and has experience as a criminal prosecutor and municipal judge. Barker has received recognition for her service to the legal profession and has been involved in various community organizations. She holds a B.A. from Notre Dame University and a J.D. from the University of Alabama School of Law.